---
import PageLayout from "../layouts/PageLayout.astro";
import business from "../config/business";
---

<PageLayout
  title="Policies"
  heading="Our Policies"
  subheading="Important information about appointments, health requirements, and more."
>
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 pb-20 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="space-y-14">
      {/* Cancellation Policy */}
      <article>
        <h2
          class="font-display text-xl font-bold text-dark border-b border-neutral-200 pb-3"
        >
          Cancellation &amp; No-Show Policy
        </h2>
        <div class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-sm text-neutral-600 leading-relaxed">
          <p>
            We understand that life happens. If you need to cancel or reschedule
            your appointment, we kindly ask for <strong class="text-dark"
              >at least 24 hours' notice</strong
            >.
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1">
            <li>Cancellations made with 24+ hours' notice: no charge.</li>
            <li>
              Cancellations made with less than 24 hours' notice: a $25 late
              cancellation fee may apply.
            </li>
            <li>
              No-shows (missed appointments without notice): the full service
              price may be charged.
            </li>
            <li>
              Repeated no-shows may result in a required deposit for future
              bookings.
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            To cancel or reschedule, please call us at
            <a
              href={`tel:${business.phone.replace(/[^+\d]/g, "")}`}
              class="text-primary-600 font-medium hover:underline"
              >{business.phone}</a
            >
            or email
            <a
              href={`mailto:${business.email}`}
              class="text-primary-600 font-medium hover:underline"
              >{business.email}</a
            >.
          </p>
        </div>
      </article>

      {/* Health & Vaccination Requirements */}
      <article>
        <h2
          class="font-display text-xl font-bold text-dark border-b border-neutral-200 pb-3"
        >
          Health &amp; Vaccination Requirements
        </h2>
        <div class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-sm text-neutral-600 leading-relaxed">
          <p>
            For the safety and well-being of all pets and staff, we require the
            following:
          </p>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-dark mt-4">Dogs</h3>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1">
            <li>Rabies vaccination (current)</li>
            <li>Distemper/Parvo (DHPP) vaccination (current)</li>
            <li>Bordetella (Kennel Cough) vaccination (current)</li>
          </ul>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-dark mt-4">Cats</h3>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1">
            <li>Rabies vaccination (current)</li>
            <li>FVRCP vaccination (current)</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            Please bring proof of vaccinations to your first appointment or have
            your veterinarian email records to <a
              href={`mailto:${business.email}`}
              class="text-primary-600 font-medium hover:underline"
              >{business.email}</a
            > in advance.
          </p>
          <p>
            Pets showing signs of illness (vomiting, diarrhea, lethargy,
            coughing, discharge, parasites) will not be groomed and will need to
            be picked up immediately. No cancellation fee applies in these
            cases.
          </p>
        </div>
      </article>

      {/* Aggressive Pet Policy */}
      <article>
        <h2
          class="font-display text-xl font-bold text-dark border-b border-neutral-200 pb-3"
        >
          Behavioral &amp; Aggressive Pet Policy
        </h2>
        <div class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-sm text-neutral-600 leading-relaxed">
          <p>
            Our groomers are experienced in gentle handling and calming nervous
            pets. However, the safety of our team is paramount.
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1">
            <li>
              Please inform us of any history of biting, aggression, or extreme
              anxiety at the time of booking.
            </li>
            <li>
              If a pet becomes aggressive during grooming, we reserve the right
              to stop the session for safety. You will be charged for the
              portion of the service completed.
            </li>
            <li>
              For anxious or reactive pets, we offer "introduction sessions" —
              short, low-pressure visits to build comfort gradually.
            </li>
            <li>
              In some cases, we may recommend consulting with your veterinarian
              about anxiety-reducing options before the appointment.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </article>

      {/* Matted Coat Policy */}
      <article>
        <h2
          class="font-display text-xl font-bold text-dark border-b border-neutral-200 pb-3"
        >
          Matted Coat Policy
        </h2>
        <div class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-sm text-neutral-600 leading-relaxed">
          <p>
            Severely matted coats can cause pain, restrict blood flow, and hide
            skin conditions. De-matting can be time-consuming, uncomfortable,
            and sometimes impossible without shaving.
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1">
            <li>We will always attempt gentle de-matting when possible.</li>
            <li>
              If matting is too severe, we may recommend a "fresh start" clip
              for your pet's comfort and safety.
            </li>
            <li>Additional charges may apply for extensive de-matting work.</li>
            <li>
              We will always discuss options and get your approval before
              proceeding.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </article>

      {/* Liability */}
      <article>
        <h2
          class="font-display text-xl font-bold text-dark border-b border-neutral-200 pb-3"
        >
          Liability Disclaimer
        </h2>
        <div class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-sm text-neutral-600 leading-relaxed">
          <p>
            While we take the utmost care with every pet, grooming does involve
            handling, bathing, cutting, and drying. There are inherent risks
            involved, including but not limited to:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1">
            <li>
              Minor nicks or scrapes (especially on matted or moving pets)
            </li>
            <li>Stress-related behaviors</li>
            <li>Pre-existing conditions becoming apparent during grooming</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            {business.name} carries professional liability insurance. In the unlikely
            event of an injury, we will immediately inform you and, if necessary,
            seek veterinary attention at our expense for any injury caused by our
            negligence.
          </p>
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</PageLayout>
